
/*
 * The provided Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to use the [add] slot to append nodes retrieved by [get-nodes] from the [.arguments] node to a specific location within a data structure. The [add] slot targets the children of the [where] node within a [data.read] operation, and [get-nodes] fetches all nodes under [.arguments] to be added. 
 * 
 * 1. [add] - Appends nodes to the specified location.
 * 2. [get-nodes] - Retrieves nodes from the [.arguments] node.
 */
add:x:./*/data.read/*/where/*
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*
